Nmap’s Scripting Engine (NSE) includes a vast number of scripts, organized into various categories. Here’s a comprehensive list of categories and some notable scripts within each:
1. Authentication

    http-auth - Checks for HTTP authentication
    http-auth-finder - Finds HTTP authentication methods
    ftp-brute - Brute-forces FTP credentials
    ssh-brute - Brute-forces SSH credentials
    smb-brute - Brute-forces SMB credentials
    snmp-brute - Brute-forces SNMP community strings
    mysql-brute - Brute-forces MySQL credentials

2. Brute Force

    http-brute - Brute-forces HTTP authentication
    imap-brute - Brute-forces IMAP credentials
    ms-sql-brute - Brute-forces MS SQL credentials
    redis-brute - Brute-forces Redis passwords
    sip-brute - Brute-forces SIP credentials
    vnc-brute - Brute-forces VNC passwords

3. Discovery

    http-enum - Enumerates directories and files on an HTTP server
    dns-brute - Performs DNS brute-forcing
    smb-enum-shares - Enumerates SMB shares
    snmp-sysdescr - Retrieves system description via SNMP
    ssh-publickey-acceptance - Checks if SSH public keys are accepted
    telnet-enum - Enumerates services via Telnet
    whois - Retrieves WHOIS information

4. Vulnerability Scanning

    http-vuln-cve2014-3704 - Tests for a specific Drupal vulnerability
    smb-vuln-ms17-010 - Tests for the SMB vulnerability exploited by WannaCry
    ssl-heartbleed - Checks for the Heartbleed vulnerability
    ssh-vuln-cve2014-2653 - Tests for an SSH vulnerability
    http-shellshock - Exploits the Shellshock vulnerability

5. Information Gathering

    http-headers - Retrieves HTTP headers
    dns-info - Gathers DNS-related information
    smtp-commands - Retrieves SMTP server commands
    snmp-info - Retrieves SNMP information
    http-title - Retrieves the title of a web page
    http-methods - Lists HTTP methods supported by a server
    ftp-syst - Retrieves system information from FTP servers

6. Exploitation

    http-shellshock - Exploits Shellshock vulnerability
    ms17-010 - Exploits the SMB vulnerability
    http-csrf - Tests for Cross-Site Request Forgery vulnerabilities
    http-sql-injection - Tests for SQL injection vulnerabilities

7. Services Enumeration

    http-service - Identifies HTTP service and version
    smtp-enum-users - Enumerates users on SMTP servers
    pop3-capabilities - Retrieves capabilities of a POP3 server
    ftp-anon - Checks for anonymous FTP access
    smb-os-discovery - Discovers operating system and domain information via SMB

8. Network Scanning

    traceroute - Performs network path tracing
    ping - Checks if a host is reachable
    ip-geolocation - Attempts to determine the geographical location of an IP address
    network-mapping - Maps network structure

9. Miscellaneous

    ssl-enum-ciphers - Enumerates SSL/TLS ciphers supported by a server
    ssl-dh-params - Checks the Diffie-Hellman parameters in SSL/TLS
    http-robots.txt - Retrieves and parses robots.txt file for interesting URLs
    http-php-version - Detects the PHP version from HTTP responses


2.To find the detail about the scripts we have two options :

	1.First is to look at the website https://nmap.org/nsedoc/categories/ 
	2.head /usr/share/nmap/scripts/script.db or grep "ftp" /usr/share/nmap/scripts/script.db

